<title type="html"><![CDATA[Emulator license?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4957&amp;p=44347#p44347"><![CDATA[
There are two main things a license achieves:<br />- Exerts whatever control you want over your work. Like whether it's sold, can be modified/derived from, etc.<br />- Protects you from legal issues when people misuse it, for example running a life support system via an emulated NES cartridge.<br /><br />So to select a license, you have to decide what control you want to exert, and what legal issues you're concerned about.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Sun Mar 15, 2009 4:59 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
